{
  "texts": [
    "Scores close to the real batch numbers denote good mixing.",
    "However, the typical iLISI score is not applicable to graph-based outputs.",
    "scIB proposed the graph iLISI, which uses a graph-based distance metric to determine the nearest neighbor list and avoids skews on graph-based integration outputs.",
    "The graph iLISI scores are scaled to [0, 1], where 0 indicates strong separation, and 1 indicates perfect mixing.",
    "Graph connectivity."
  ]
}